def: A beverage made of wine, water, sugar, nutmeg, and lemon juice;-- so called, it is said, from its first maker, Colonel Negus.
Pertaining to, produced by, or attending, catarrh; of thenature of catarrh.
The act of refunding; also, that which is refunded. [R.] Lamb.

A mound of earth or a platform in a fortification, on whichguns are mounted to fire over the parapet. En barbette, In barbette,said of guns when they are elevated so as to fire over the top of aparapet, and not through embrasures.-- Barbette gun, or Barbette battery, a single gun, or a number ofguns, mounted in barbette, or partially protected by a parapet orturret.-- Barbette carriage, a gun carriage which elevates gunssufficiently to be in barbette. [See Illust. of Casemate.]
A salt of oenanthylic acid; as, potassium oenanthylate.
Having two coverings, a calyx and in corolla.
Encompassing on all sides; circumfused; investing. "Ambientair." Milton. "Ambient clouds." Pope.
A strong malt liquor; strong porter. Swift.
